               <p>SARAH THOMAS. I am a <rs id="t18280911-375-viclabel1945" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-375-victim2025 t18280911-375-viclabel1945"></join> and I live in <placeName id="t18280911-375-crimeloc1946">Whitecross-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-375-crimeloc1946" type="placeName" value="Whitecross-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-375-crimeloc1946" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-375-off1943 t18280911-375-crimeloc1946"></join>. The prisoner Smith took a room of me for herself, her husband, and child; when they had been there a week I found she did not live with her husband - she staid there about three weeks; I did not live in the house - I received information, went to the house, and found Smith was not there; I found a key to fit the door, I got in, and missed these articles - I once saw Brooks there, but not when the things were taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-375-person2026">
                  MARY 
                  FLOWERS
               <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2026" type="surname" value="FLOWERS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2026" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2026" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a widow. I live in the house with the prosecutrix; I saw Brooks in a shed with the water-butt in his hand; I do not know when it was.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-375-person2027">
                  ELIZABETH 
                  WEAVER
               <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2027" type="surname" value="WEAVER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2027" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2027" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a widow. On the 17th of July, Smith came to me and said she was going into the country for ten weeks, and asked me to take care of a bed, a bolster, some chairs, and a little crockery, and she would give me 4d. a week - Brooks soon after brought a bed; I said, "You are not the person I agreed to take it of, without her I will have nothing to do with it;" she came directly after, and said it was all right - I took it in, but had nothing more.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-375-person2028">
                  THOMAS 
                  ELMER
               <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2028" type="surname" value="ELMER"></interp>
