                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2029" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I found the prisoners at a house in Crown-court, Golden-lane, both intoxicated.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-375-person2030">
                  JOHN 
                  TOWNLEY
               <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2030" type="surname" value="TOWNLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2030" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-375-person2030" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I assisted in taking Smith to the watch-house; on the road she said money would be no object, and I think mentioned a sovereign.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>BROOKS' Defence. I never knew but they were Smith's things - I carried them for her, as she said she wanted money.</p>
               <p>ELIZABETH SMITH's Defence. The man did not know but they were my own - I was in great distress.</p>
